node.text: No days off ,Happy holidays . shoutout to @liambadco @hansmolenkamp @filipposolheid @samingdech55  for always keeping me motivated
Me and my favorite hoodie and my favorite poster by my  NY brother @yuryshats  at the Mecca of pizza @scarrspizza . If you ain’t got loyalty you ain’t got shit , shoutout to all my real ones .

There are many beautiful and expensive things in this world . But the symbol of these  two objects are worth more than all the riches in the world to me . My gloves that have travelled the world with me , signed by my brother and Muay Thai trainer @samingdech55 with my thai name given to me by my gym in Koh samui , the gloves that my boxing sensei and brother @rotheshow had to teach me how to box from scratch . They are not the nicest gloves but they are mine and I have earned them . The other is my blue belt which my sensei and brother #joshgriffiths @clockworkbjj gave me . These might just look like trash to many but these are the most precious things I own , I have sweat , bled , broken bones for these and I wouldn’t trade them for anything . In a world of smoke in mirrors , martial arts are a safe haven for hard work and honesty. A place where people from all different backgrounds come to try and improve themselves thru hard work , respect and honor.  It felt important to me to speak to this at this time of year when we are surrounded and drenched in consumerism. All I asked for Christmas  is  the health and happiness of my loved ones and training partners . I know I get emo pretty often here , but I can whole heartedly say that martial arts saved my life. Thank you to everyone who has supported me in this journey you might not know how much you’ve done but I remember every piece of advice given and every pat on the back . Sign your kids up for martial arts , you will make the world a better place . Happy holidays to everyone , let’s consume a little less and be present with each other and love one another a lil bit more ❤️ PMA forever .
